The Senate today confirmed all 43 ministerial nominees presented by President Muhammadu Buhari on july 23rd 2019. The upper legislative chamber confirmed the nominees after concluding screening of the Ministerial Nominees, calling out nominees names and putting the questions to vote.  In his speech at the end of the confirmation process, the Senate President, Dr Ahmad Lawan urged the minister-designates to work closely with lawmakers because the oversight functions of the National Assembly was sacrosanct.  According to him, days of turning down invitation to appear before legislative committees were over, adding that the 9th Senate would not be frivolous in the discharge of its activities. Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Senate President expressed optimism that the annual budget would be presented to the National Assembly by the Executive, first or last week of September, so that the country would revert to the January to December fiscal year.  The nominees confirmed are; Rotimi Amaechi (Rivers), Lai Mohammed (Kwara), Raji Fasola (Lagos) Geofrey Onyema (Enugu) Adamu Adamu (Bauchi) Chris Ngige (Anambra) Abubakar Malami (Kebbi), Sule Ogbonnaya Onu (Ebonyi) Zainab Ahmed (Kaduna) Hadi Sirika (Katsina) and Osagie Ehanire (Edo) and others.